# Coin Flip Simulation

## Question
How does the proportion of heads change as the number of coin flips increases?

## Method
I simulated fair coin flips using Python. I compared different sample sizes, tracked the running proportion of heads over time, and measured the longest streaks of heads and tails.

## Result
Small samples varied widely from 50% heads. Larger samples became more stable and moved closer to 0.5.

## What I Learned
This simulation demonstrates the law of large numbers. Random outcomes can look uneven in the short run, but long-run proportions tend to approach the expected probability.